WEBVTT

00:33.033 --> 00:34.909
TV: Coin collecting is considered
the perfect hobby.

00:34.993 --> 00:35.827
Beautiful putt right there...

00:35.911 --> 00:36.744
Good birdie.

00:36.829 --> 00:39.122
That's only the...
eighth birdie of the day.

00:39.206 --> 00:40.623
What?

00:40.708 --> 00:41.749
Why are you looking at me?

00:41.834 --> 00:43.418
You want to go outside?

00:43.502 --> 00:44.711
Outside?

00:44.795 --> 00:45.962
[ TV shuts off ]

00:46.046 --> 00:47.588
[ sighs ]

00:47.673 --> 00:49.006
Outside?

00:54.638 --> 00:55.680
Are you kidding me?! Come on!

00:55.764 --> 00:56.639
Oh, my God.

00:56.724 --> 00:57.724
W-what's wrong?

00:57.725 --> 00:58.725
Your idiot dog!

00:58.767 --> 01:00.518
Oh, he...
he didn't mean it, Dad.

01:00.602 --> 01:01.436
D-did you, Snuffles?

01:01.520 --> 01:02.395
You're a good boy.

01:02.479 --> 01:04.147
Don't praise him now, Morty!

01:04.231 --> 01:05.106
He just peed on the carpet!

01:05.190 --> 01:06.190
Bad dog! Bad!

01:06.191 --> 01:07.191
Morty, come on.

01:07.192 --> 01:08.192
I need your help tonight.

01:08.193 --> 01:09.944
Hey, wait, hold on a second,
Rick.

01:10.028 --> 01:12.548
You wouldn't by any chance have
some sort of crazy science thing

01:12.614 --> 01:14.240
you could whip up that might
help make this dog a little

01:14.324 --> 01:15.575
smarter, would you?

01:15.659 --> 01:17.118
I thought the whole point
of having a dog was to

01:17.202 --> 01:18.369
feel superior, Jerry.

01:18.454 --> 01:19.662
If I were you,
I wouldn't pull that thread.

01:19.747 --> 01:20.955
Come on, Morty.

01:21.039 --> 01:23.791
Listen, Rick, if you're
gonna stay here rent-free

01:23.876 --> 01:26.002
and use my son for
your stupid science,

01:26.086 --> 01:28.546
the least you could do is
put a little bit of it to use

01:28.630 --> 01:29.797
for the family.

01:29.882 --> 01:31.716
You make that dog smart or...

01:31.800 --> 01:32.633
Morty's grounded!

01:32.718 --> 01:34.135
Ha-ha! Aw, man!

01:34.219 --> 01:36.971
Boy, you really got me up
against a wall this time, Jerry.

01:37.055 --> 01:38.175
[ door opens, bells jingle ]

01:38.182 --> 01:39.766
[ machine whirs ]

01:41.894 --> 01:43.374
All right, Ruffles...
What's his name?

01:43.437 --> 01:44.270
Snuffles.

01:44.354 --> 01:46.647
Snuffles, shake.

01:46.732 --> 01:48.524
Roll over.

01:48.609 --> 01:51.569
Go to the bathroom.

01:51.653 --> 01:52.528
[ toilet flushes ]

01:52.613 --> 01:54.238
- Holy crap!
- No way.

01:54.323 --> 01:57.200
Yeah, you're at the top
of your game now, Jerry.

01:57.284 --> 01:58.159
Have fun.

01:58.243 --> 01:59.076
Come on, Morty.

01:59.161 --> 02:00.286
That was fantastic, Rick!

02:00.370 --> 02:01.829
Yeah, Morty, if you

02:01.914 --> 02:03.581
like that, boy, you're... you're
really going to flip your lid

02:03.665 --> 02:04.499
over this one.

02:04.583 --> 02:05.958
W-w-w-what is it?

02:06.043 --> 02:08.461
It's a device, Morty, that
when you put it in your ear,

02:08.545 --> 02:10.087
you can enter
people's dreams, Morty.

02:10.172 --> 02:12.292
It's just like that movie that
you keep crowing about.

02:12.299 --> 02:13.883
You talking about "Inception"?

02:13.967 --> 02:15.718
That's right, Morty.
This is gonna be a lot like

02:15.803 --> 02:17.845
that, except, you know, it's
gonna [burps] maybe make sense.

02:17.930 --> 02:19.180
"Inception" made sense.

02:19.264 --> 02:20.765
You don't have to
try to impress me, Morty.

02:20.849 --> 02:22.725
Listen, tonight we're gonna go
into the home of your math teacher,

02:22.810 --> 02:24.894
Mr. Goldenfold, and
we're g... we're gonna incept

02:24.978 --> 02:27.939
the idea in his brain to give
you A's in math, Morty.

02:28.023 --> 02:29.482
That way you can, you know...

02:29.566 --> 02:31.926
y-you're gonna help me with my
science, Morty, all the time.

02:31.985 --> 02:33.611
Geez, Rick, in the time it
took you to make this thing,

02:33.695 --> 02:34.737
couldn't you have just,

02:34.822 --> 02:36.364
you know, helped me
with my homework?

02:36.448 --> 02:37.698
Are you listening to me, Morty?

02:37.783 --> 02:38.783
Homework is stupid.

02:38.826 --> 02:40.451
The whole point is
to get less of it.

02:40.536 --> 02:42.119
J-J... come on,
let... j...

02:42.204 --> 02:43.746
let's just get over there
and deal with this thing.

02:43.831 --> 02:45.456
W-we're gonna incept
your teacher.

02:45.541 --> 02:47.917
Y-y-y-y-y-you're
frustrating me.

02:48.001 --> 02:49.460
[ engine turns over ]

02:51.547 --> 02:53.214
You don't know me!

02:53.298 --> 02:56.425
Nice, Mrs. Pancakes...
real nice.

02:56.510 --> 02:59.470
Next week on "The Days And
Nights Of Mrs. Pancakes"...

02:59.555 --> 03:00.555
[ snoring ]

03:00.556 --> 03:01.639
You don't know me!

03:01.723 --> 03:04.225
Then let me get to know you,
damn it!

03:04.309 --> 03:05.893
Uh-oh! Spoilers!

03:05.978 --> 03:07.812
I'm a full season behind.

03:07.896 --> 03:09.438
Wow, Rick, I can't believe
we're sitting around,

03:09.523 --> 03:11.858
standing around in
Mr. Goldenfold's house.

03:11.942 --> 03:12.942
It's really weird.

03:12.985 --> 03:14.235
[ device whirs ]

03:14.319 --> 03:15.736
It's about to get a whole
lot weirder, Morty.

03:15.821 --> 03:20.074
[ device whirs ]

03:21.410 --> 03:22.410
[ indistinct conversations ]

03:22.494 --> 03:24.662
Wheat Thins. Wheat Thins.

03:24.746 --> 03:25.913
I'll take two.

03:25.998 --> 03:27.957
Oh, I think you've
had enough, sir.

03:28.041 --> 03:29.041
You don't know me.

03:29.126 --> 03:31.002
[ both laugh ]

03:31.086 --> 03:33.421
All right, Morty,
time to make our move.

03:33.505 --> 03:35.214
Make it bounce.

03:35.299 --> 03:36.340
No, you didn't.

03:36.425 --> 03:37.300
Oh, jiggle it now.

03:37.384 --> 03:38.509
You better stop with that.

03:38.594 --> 03:40.761
Allahu [burps] Akbar!

03:40.846 --> 03:42.366
We're gonna take control
of this plane!

03:42.431 --> 03:44.432
We're gonna 9/1 1 it unless
Morty Smith gets better grades

03:44.516 --> 03:45.391
in math!

03:45.475 --> 03:46.715
Hey! I said nobody move, buddy!

03:46.768 --> 03:48.102
The name's not buddy.

03:48.186 --> 03:49.604
It's Goldenfold.

03:49.688 --> 03:51.230
Nice to wheat you!

03:51.315 --> 03:53.357
[ grunts ]

03:53.442 --> 03:55.401
Take cover, Morty!

03:55.485 --> 03:56.777
[ passengers screaming ]

03:56.862 --> 03:58.237
[ screams ]

03:58.322 --> 03:59.322
Ooh!

03:59.406 --> 04:01.526
Goldenfold's got more control
here than I anticipated.

04:01.533 --> 04:02.617
I mean, the guy teaches
high-school math.

04:02.701 --> 04:03.701
[ burps ]

04:03.702 --> 04:05.578
l-I-I-l didn't take him
for an active dreamer.

04:05.662 --> 04:07.538
We got to take him out
so he wakes up, Morty.

04:07.623 --> 04:08.956
But we can't get killed.

04:09.041 --> 04:10.374
If you get killed in
someone else's dream,

04:10.459 --> 04:12.001
you die for real, Morty.

04:12.085 --> 04:13.165
What?! Are you kidding me?!

04:13.170 --> 04:14.170
Ohhhhhh!

04:14.254 --> 04:15.546
Don't be a baby!

04:15.631 --> 04:17.548
You avoid getting shot in real
life all the time, Morty.

04:17.633 --> 04:19.508
Just do the same thing here,
and we'll be fine!

04:19.593 --> 04:21.594
Now bring me my slippers.

04:21.678 --> 04:25.348
Now, be my footstool, Snuffles.

04:25.432 --> 04:26.933
This is what I'm talking about.

04:27.017 --> 04:28.935
This is a dog.

04:29.019 --> 04:29.936
[ sarcastically ] Oh, yeah.

04:30.020 --> 04:31.729
This should play out just fine.

04:31.813 --> 04:34.482
You said the same thing,
equally sarcastically,

04:34.566 --> 04:36.067
at our wedding and guess what.

04:42.240 --> 04:44.742
[ howling ]

04:44.826 --> 04:45.868
Oh, my God.

04:45.953 --> 04:47.119
He's trying to tell
us something.

04:47.204 --> 04:48.537
That is so awesome.

04:48.622 --> 04:51.207
[ howling ]

04:51.291 --> 04:53.668
Aw, he's saying
"I love lasagna."

04:53.752 --> 04:54.961
[ groans ]

04:55.045 --> 04:57.505
[ howling ]

04:57.589 --> 04:59.173
He's saying
"I love Obama."

04:59.257 --> 05:00.591
[ camera shutter clicks ]
So cute!

05:00.676 --> 05:02.718
I'm posting this online,
like, right now.

05:02.803 --> 05:04.220
I should call Bob Saget.

05:04.304 --> 05:05.554
Is that still a thing?

05:05.639 --> 05:07.098
[ sighs ]

05:15.691 --> 05:16.899
Hmm?

05:23.949 --> 05:24.949
[ passengers screaming ]

05:24.992 --> 05:26.242
Goldenfold, we're coming out!

05:26.326 --> 05:27.326
We just want to talk!

05:27.327 --> 05:28.786
Why would I negotiate with you?

05:28.870 --> 05:31.539
Because we're both rational
adults that don't want anything

05:31.623 --> 05:32.623
bad to happen.

05:32.708 --> 05:34.041
And because I
have a human shield.

05:34.126 --> 05:35.126
Mrs. Pancakes!

05:35.127 --> 05:36.877
[ screams ]

05:36.962 --> 05:38.587
[ passengers screaming ]

05:38.672 --> 05:39.505
Oh, no, Morty.

05:39.589 --> 05:40.798
His subconscious is panicking.

05:40.882 --> 05:42.383
Run!

05:42.467 --> 05:47.888
[ all screaming ]

05:50.142 --> 05:51.142
[ slap! ]
Relax, Morty.

05:51.143 --> 05:51.976
Look!

05:52.060 --> 05:53.260
Mrs. Pancakes has a parachute.

05:53.270 --> 05:54.395
Come on!

05:54.479 --> 05:56.772
Hey, you don't know me!

05:56.857 --> 05:58.232
Oh, no, Rick, look!

05:58.316 --> 05:59.692
Goldenfold landed the plane,

05:59.776 --> 06:01.819
and he's created a mechanical
arm to pluck Mrs. Pancakes

06:01.903 --> 06:04.655
out of the air while he lets us
fall into a giant vat of lava!

06:04.740 --> 06:05.948
Pretty concise, Morty.

06:06.033 --> 06:07.825
Looks like we've merely
prolonged the inevitable.

06:07.909 --> 06:08.993
That's it, Morty!

06:09.077 --> 06:10.202
Prolonging the inevitable!

06:10.287 --> 06:12.079
Listen, if we go into Mrs.
Pancakes' dream,

06:12.164 --> 06:14.290
everything will go
100 times slower, Morty.

06:14.374 --> 06:15.833
That'll buy us some time to
figure this out!

06:15.917 --> 06:16.917
You don't know m...

06:19.755 --> 06:21.547
All right, let's go.

06:21.631 --> 06:22.423
[ device whirs ]

06:22.507 --> 06:24.216
[ upbeat music plays ]

06:26.511 --> 06:27.803
[ gnomes giggling ]

06:27.888 --> 06:29.889
MORTY:
Oh, man, Rick, this is pretty weird.

06:29.973 --> 06:31.640
Don't judge, Morty.

06:31.725 --> 06:32.725
Okay.

06:32.726 --> 06:34.268
All right, well...
- [ grunting ]

06:34.352 --> 06:35.686
Look, Mrs. Pancakes
is right over there.

06:35.771 --> 06:37.313
I'll just go ask her to tell
Goldenfold not to kill us

06:37.397 --> 06:38.689
when she wakes up.

06:38.774 --> 06:41.294
Whoa, whoa, Morty, the trick to
incepting is making people think

06:41.359 --> 06:42.526
they came up with the idea.

06:42.611 --> 06:43.986
Listen to me.

06:44.071 --> 06:46.530
If we're gonna incept Mrs.
Pancakes, we have to blend.

06:46.615 --> 06:48.491
I'll talk to you after lunch.

06:48.575 --> 06:49.784
[ gnomes giggling ]

06:49.868 --> 06:51.577
Ooh, hey!

06:51.661 --> 06:52.661
[ whimpers ]

06:52.746 --> 06:53.788
Ooh, oh!

06:53.872 --> 06:54.997
Oh, man.

06:55.082 --> 06:56.999
- Come and join us.
- I'm sorry. No, no.

06:57.084 --> 06:58.459
- Ooh, come here!
- No, thanks!

06:58.543 --> 06:59.919
Ooh, wow!
Come over here, baby!

07:00.003 --> 07:01.295
No, I'm okay.

07:01.379 --> 07:04.298
Whoa!

07:04.382 --> 07:05.841
Summer?!

07:05.926 --> 07:07.009
Hey, there, stranger.

07:07.094 --> 07:08.719
What do you think
of these things?

07:08.804 --> 07:10.596
Ohh! Oh! Gross!

07:10.680 --> 07:11.764
Gross!

07:11.848 --> 07:13.057
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

07:13.141 --> 07:14.600
What's the matter with you,
Morty? Calm down!

07:14.684 --> 07:16.143
You're kind of killing
the vibe in here.

07:16.228 --> 07:17.228
It's S-S-S-Summer!

07:17.312 --> 07:18.729
Aw, geez.

07:18.814 --> 07:21.148
Looks like Goldenfold has some
predilections so shameful he

07:21.233 --> 07:23.150
buries them in the dreams
of the people in his dreams,

07:23.235 --> 07:25.569
including a pervy attraction
to your underage sister.

07:25.654 --> 07:27.154
Can you blame him?

07:27.239 --> 07:28.614
Come on, old man, little boy.

07:28.698 --> 07:31.367
Let's make an
inter-generational sandwich.

07:31.451 --> 07:33.327
Oh, my God. Oh, my God!

07:33.411 --> 07:34.851
Put some clothes on,
for pete's sake!

07:34.871 --> 07:35.955
This is disgusting!

07:36.039 --> 07:36.914
I'm gonna puke!

07:36.998 --> 07:38.749
I can't take it, Rick!

07:38.834 --> 07:41.961
Sexual hang-ups in the pleasure
chamber are punishable by death!

07:42.045 --> 07:43.170
Off with their heads!

07:43.255 --> 07:45.714
Time to go another
dream deep, Morty!

07:45.799 --> 07:46.799
[ grunts ]

07:46.842 --> 07:48.759
[ exhales ]

07:48.844 --> 07:51.762
[ device whirs ]

07:53.140 --> 07:54.807
[ whimpers ] What the hell?

07:54.891 --> 07:57.768
Why would Mr. Goldenfold's dream
version of Mrs. Pancakes' dream

07:57.853 --> 08:00.146
version of a Centaur be dreaming

08:00.230 --> 08:01.772
about a scary place
like this, Rick?

08:01.857 --> 08:02.731
Geez, I don't know, Morty.

08:02.816 --> 08:03.976
Wha-what do you want from me?

08:03.984 --> 08:06.777
[ metal scraping ]

08:06.862 --> 08:08.821
Welcome to your nightmare,
bitch!

08:08.905 --> 08:10.906
Oh, here we go!

08:10.991 --> 08:12.366
Holy crap!

08:12.450 --> 08:14.785
Looks like some sort of legally
safe knock-off of an '80s horror

08:14.870 --> 08:17.621
character with miniature swords
for fingers instead of knives.

08:17.706 --> 08:19.623
I'm Scary Terry.

08:19.708 --> 08:21.876
You can run,
but you can't hide, bitch!

08:23.712 --> 08:25.588
Whoa! Hey, buddy.

08:25.672 --> 08:27.214
What you got going on there?

08:27.299 --> 08:28.716
[ robotic ] Snuffles fix.

08:28.800 --> 08:30.050
Make better.

08:30.135 --> 08:32.303
Humans understand Snuffles now?

08:32.387 --> 08:34.680
That... is... awesome!

08:34.764 --> 08:37.099
Snuffles want to be understood.

08:37.184 --> 08:39.560
Snuffles need to be understood.

08:39.644 --> 08:41.187
Okay, yeah.

08:41.271 --> 08:42.938
I get what Beth
was talking about.

08:43.023 --> 08:44.106
Fun's over.

08:44.191 --> 08:45.399
Whoa, Dad, you can't, like,

08:45.483 --> 08:47.693
endow a creature with
sentience and then rip it away.

08:47.777 --> 08:48.611
Why not?

08:48.695 --> 08:49.528
I don't know.

08:49.613 --> 08:52.156
It's Indian giving.

08:52.240 --> 08:54.992
A sophisticated predator,
nature's perfect killing

08:55.076 --> 08:58.537
machine, the vicious wolf
stalks its prey with purpose

08:58.622 --> 09:00.122
and skill.

09:00.207 --> 09:03.000
It was only with years of
selective breeding and genetic

09:03.084 --> 09:06.795
altering that this noble beast
was transformed into man's

09:06.880 --> 09:09.673
subservient little buddy.

09:13.803 --> 09:16.138
Aw! Oh, my God!

09:16.223 --> 09:19.099
He recognizes the
other dogs on TV.

09:21.102 --> 09:22.102
♪ "A," "B" ♪

09:22.145 --> 09:23.854
♪ His name is Scary Terry ♪

09:23.939 --> 09:24.730
[ screams ]

09:24.814 --> 09:25.981
♪ "C," "D" ♪

09:26.066 --> 09:27.233
♪ He's very scary ♪

09:27.317 --> 09:28.734
Holy crap!

09:28.818 --> 09:30.611
We have to escape into
someone else's dreams, Morty!

09:30.695 --> 09:32.112
Ohhhhh!

09:32.197 --> 09:34.782
Oh, man, oh, man, oh, man!

09:34.866 --> 09:36.242
♪ "E," "F" ♪

09:36.326 --> 09:38.786
♪ He'll design your death ♪

09:38.870 --> 09:40.162
The little girl!

09:40.247 --> 09:42.873
[ device whirs ]

09:42.958 --> 09:43.749
Huh?

09:43.833 --> 09:45.042
[ gasps ]

09:45.126 --> 09:46.877
♪ "J," "K,"
He'll really ruin your day ♪

09:46.962 --> 09:48.337
Are you kidding me?
This again?

09:48.421 --> 09:50.297
Oh, man, it looks like we've
hit dream bedrock here, Morty.

09:50.382 --> 09:51.382
Oh, geez, Rick.

09:51.383 --> 09:52.466
W-w-whoa, this isn't good.

09:52.550 --> 09:54.843
Nothing but fear from
here on out, bitch!

09:54.928 --> 09:55.803
Ohhhh!

09:55.887 --> 09:56.720
Holy crap, Morty.

09:56.805 --> 09:58.013
He can travel through dreams.

09:58.098 --> 09:59.640
He can travel through dreams!

09:59.724 --> 10:01.141
We're so screwed!

10:01.226 --> 10:04.853
[ thunder crashing ]

10:08.817 --> 10:10.192
[ gasps ]

10:10.277 --> 10:12.319
Where are my testicles, Summer?

10:14.990 --> 10:17.324
Where are my testicles, Summer?

10:17.409 --> 10:18.409
They were removed.

10:18.493 --> 10:19.994
Where have they gone?

10:20.078 --> 10:21.662
Oh, wow.

10:21.746 --> 10:24.164
That's an intense line of
questioning, Snuffles.

10:24.249 --> 10:25.749
Do not call me that!

10:25.834 --> 10:27.084
[ screams ]

10:27.168 --> 10:29.086
"Snuffles" was my slave name.

10:29.170 --> 10:32.381
You shall now call me Snowball
because my fur is pretty

10:32.465 --> 10:33.590
and white.

10:33.675 --> 10:36.885
Okay, Snowball,
just calm down, okay?

10:36.970 --> 10:37.970
You're scaring me.

10:38.013 --> 10:39.263
Scaring you?

10:39.347 --> 10:43.017
Tell me, Summer, if a human
was born with stumpy legs,

10:43.101 --> 10:45.102
would they breed it with
another deformed human

10:45.186 --> 10:48.397
and put their children on
display like the Dachshund?

10:48.481 --> 10:49.356
Uhhh...

10:49.441 --> 10:50.274
Hey.

10:50.358 --> 10:52.026
[ gasps ] Oh, wow.

10:52.110 --> 10:53.870
Okay, is... is...
is everything okay in here?

10:53.903 --> 10:56.363
Jerry, come to rub my
face in urine again?

10:56.448 --> 10:57.823
No!

10:57.907 --> 11:02.328
No, we were... uh, just seeing
if Summer wanted to ...uh...

11:02.412 --> 11:05.581
Go on, um, one of our famous
midnight family walks!

11:05.665 --> 11:06.957
Yeah. Totally.

11:07.042 --> 11:08.042
Let's go.

11:10.795 --> 11:14.590
You will walk when it
is time to walk.

11:15.258 --> 11:17.051
[ bird caws ]

11:19.596 --> 11:21.388
What are we here for again?
Incepting?

11:21.473 --> 11:23.682
We're trying to incept
me to get an "A" in math?

11:23.767 --> 11:24.850
Oh, yeah.

11:24.934 --> 11:26.477
[ engine turns over ]

11:26.561 --> 11:27.978
Buckle up, bitch!

11:28.063 --> 11:29.980
[ screams ]

11:30.065 --> 11:31.857
Man, he sure says "Bitch" a lot!

11:31.941 --> 11:34.526
You can run,
but you can't hide, bitch!

11:34.611 --> 11:36.612
Hold on, Morty.
Y-you know what?

11:36.696 --> 11:39.031
He keeps saying we can
run but we can't hide.

11:39.115 --> 11:40.282
I say we try hiding.

11:40.367 --> 11:41.742
But that's the
opposite of what...

11:41.826 --> 11:43.744
Yeah, well, since when are
we taking this guy's advice on anything?

11:43.828 --> 11:44.828
Hey, you know what?

11:44.829 --> 11:46.389
You got a really
good point there, Rick.

11:46.456 --> 11:49.124
Like, if the truth was that we
could hide, it's not like

11:49.209 --> 11:51.335
he'd be sharing that
information with us, you know?

11:51.419 --> 11:53.879
I-I-I think it's a good idea,
Rick.

11:53.963 --> 11:54.963
Worst-case scenario...

11:55.006 --> 11:56.507
we're back to running.

12:01.096 --> 12:02.721
Wow, you know what?

12:02.806 --> 12:04.556
